---
const items = [
	{
		q: 'Is it really free?',
		a: 'Yes for writing — the local editor, import/export, version history, and workspace tools are free in the open-source app. Future cloud sync, managed AI, and collaboration may be paid add-ons.',
	},
	{
		q: "Where is my script stored?",
		a: 'In your browser\'s IndexedDB on your device by default. Nothing is uploaded unless you opt into cloud features when they ship.',
	},
	{
		q: 'Does the AI train on my writing?',
		a: 'No — with BYOK, your browser sends prompts to your provider with your key. Dastan does not run a training pipeline on your scripts in the open-source app.',
	},
	{
		q: 'Can I open Final Draft files?',
		a: 'Yes — import .fdx. Keep a backup of the original; complex production metadata may not round-trip perfectly.',
	},
	{
		q: 'What if Dastan disappears?',
		a: 'Export to Fountain or FDX regularly. The code is AGPL. Your formats are industry-standard.',
	},
	{
		q: 'What does AGPL mean for me as a writer?',
		a: 'Nothing about your scripts — you own your writing. AGPL applies to the software itself if someone redistributes modified versions.',
	},
];
---

<section class="faq reveal" id="faq">
	<p class="slugline section-slug">INT. QUESTIONS — LATER</p>
	<h2 class="section-title">FAQ</h2>
	<div class="faq__list">
		{
			items.map((item) => (
				<details class="faq__item">
					<summary>{item.q}</summary>
					<p>{item.a}</p>
				</details>
			))
		}
	</div>
</section>

<style>
	.faq {
		padding: 4rem 1.25rem;
		max-width: 48rem;
		margin: 0 auto;
	}

	.faq__list {
		display: grid;
		gap: 0.65rem;
	}

	.faq__item {
		border: 1px solid #292524;
		border-radius: 0.45rem;
		background: var(--ink-soft);
		padding: 0.65rem 0.85rem;
	}

	.faq__item summary {
		cursor: pointer;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: var(--paper);
	}

	.faq__item p {
		margin: 0.65rem 0 0.15rem;
		color: #d6d3d1;
		font-size: 0.92rem;
	}
</style>
